First, Base Case: Initialize the sequence with the first element tri(1) = 3.
Second, Even Case: For even n, tri(n) = 1 + n / 2.
Third, Odd Case: For odd n, tri(n) = tri(n - 1) + tri(n - 2) + tri(n + 1).

